    "en": {
      "title": "PNS Taimur on Passage Exercise with SL Navy",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Pakistan Navy Ship (PNS) Taimur which arrived in Sri Lanka on a formal visit, is scheduled to conduct a Passage Exercise with SLNS Sindurala in the seas off Colombo as she departs the island on 15th August 2022, upon completion of her visit.",
        "Sri Lanka Navy, with the concurrence of foreign navies, conducts Passage Exercises as a routine engagement when their visiting naval ships depart the island after making official port calls.",
        "As part of this Passage Exercise, PNS Taimur and SLNS Sindurala are expected to conduct Maneuvering exercises and Search and Rescue exercises.",
        "Meanwhile, Sri Lanka Navy has conducted similar Passage Exercises with the navies of countries such as India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Japan, Germany, the U.K., Russia, and Australia on several previous occasions."
      ],
